        <h2 id="h.3znysh7" ><span class="c15 c24">RISK DICLOSURES</span></h2>
    <p class="c46"><span class="c0">Last Updated: September 5</span><span class="c28 c16">th</span><span class="c0">, &nbsp;2017</span></p>
    <ol class="c1 lst-kix_list_16-0 start" start="1">
      <li class="c32"><span class="c2">Risk of Losing Access to MTX Due to Wallet Incompatibility: </span><span class="c0">A valid ERC20 Ethereum address from an ERC20 compatible wallet like Parity, Mist, MyEtherWallet, or Metamask is required to receive your MTX because your MTX will be delivered to this address. Non-ERC20 compatible wallet addresses will not be accepted. &nbsp;In addition, the Ethereum address used must not be associated with a third party exchange or service that has custody over the private key. &nbsp;You must own the private key if your address is an exchange address. &nbsp;</span></li>
      <li class="c19"><span class="c2">Risks Associated with the Ethereum Protocol: </span><span class="c0">MTX and the Matryx platform are based on the Ethereum protocol. As such, any malfunction, unintended function, unexpected functioning of or attack on the Ethereum protocol may cause the Matryx platform or MTX to malfunction or function in an unexpected or unintended manner. Ether, the native unit of account of the Ethereum protocol, may itself lose value in ways similar to MTX, and also other ways.</span></li>
      <li class="c19"><span class="c2">Risks Associated with Purchaser Credentials: </span><span class="c0">Any third party that gains access to or learns of your wallet login credentials or private keys may be able to dispose of your MTX. To minimize this risk, you should guard against unauthorized access to your electronic devices.. Best practices dictate that you safely store private keys in one or more backup locations geographically separated from the working location. &nbsp;In addition, you are responsible for giving us the correct address to send you your MTX. &nbsp;If you give us the incorrect address to send your MTX to, we are not responsible for any loss of MTX that may occur.</span></li>
      <li class="c20"><span class="c2">Risk of Unfavorable Regulatory Action in One or More Jurisdictions: </span><span class="c0">&nbsp;Blockchain technologies and token sales have been the subject of scrutiny by various regulatory bodies around the world. The functioning of the Matryx platform and MTX could be impacted by one or more regulatory inquiries or actions, including the licensing of or restrictions on the use, sale, or possession of digital tokens like MTX, which could impede, limit or end the development of the Matryx platform and increase legal costs.</span></li>
      <li class="c19"><span class="c2">Risk of Alternative, Unofficial Matryx platform: </span><span class="c0">Following the Token Issuance Program and the development of the initial version of the MTX platform, it is possible that alternative applications could be established, which use the same open source code and protocol underlying the Matryx platform. The official Matryx platform may compete with these alternative, unofficial MTX-based applications, which could potentially negatively impact the Matryx platform and MTX, including its value.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <p class="c36 c13"><span class="c44 c16"></span></p>
    <ol class="c1 lst-kix_list_16-0" start="6">
      <li class="c52"><span class="c15">Risk of Insufficient Interest in the Matryx platform or Distributed Applications: </span><span class="c0">It is possible that the Matryx platform will not be used by a large number of businesses, individuals, and other organizations and that there will be limited public interest in the creation and development of distributed applications. Such a lack of interest could negatively impact MTX and the Matryx platform.</span></li>
      <li class="c22"><span class="c2">Risk that the Matryx platform, As Developed, Will Not Meet the Expectations of Matryx or the Purchaser: </span><span class="c0">The Matryx platform is presently under development and may undergo significant changes before release. Any expectations or assumptions regarding the form and functionality of the Matryx platform or MTX (including participant behavior) held by Matryx or the purchaser may not be met upon release, for any number of reasons including mistaken assumptions or analysis, a change in the design and implementation plans and execution of the Matryx platform.</span></li>
      <li class="c22"><span class="c2">Risk of Unfavorable Fluctuation of Ether and Other Currency Value: </span><span class="c0">The Company team correctly intends to use the proceeds from selling MTX to fund the maintenance and development of the Matryx platform, as described further in the White Paper. The proceeds of the Token Issuance Program will be denominated in Ether, and converted into other cryptographic and fiat currencies. If the value of Ether or other currencies fluctuates unfavorably during or after the Token Issuance Program, the Company team may not be able to fund development, or may not be able to develop or maintain the Matryx platform in the manner that it intended.</span></li>
      <li class="c22"><span class="c2">Risks from Taxation: </span><span class="c0">The tax characterization of MTX is uncertain. You must seek your own tax advice in connection with purchasing MTX, which may result in adverse tax consequences to you, including withholding taxes, income taxes, and tax reporting requirements.</span></li>
